<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" class="tborder" width="100%">
<tr>
<td class="tcat"><span class="smallfont"><b>&raquo; Epic 1.0 Walkthrough Part 3</b></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="alt2">

<h1>Cleric Epic 1.0</h1>
<span style="font-size:11px"><a href="index.php?page=epic101">1</a>
<a href="index.php?page=epic102">2</a> 3 <a href="index.php?page=epic104">4</a>
</span><br>
<strong>Original walkthrough by Walbort<br>
Updated by Boanerges Thundercry<br>
Special thanks to Shelsea Druid for compiling these newest steps in <a href="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?t=9483">this thread</a></strong>
<hr>
<h2>Part 3: Orb of Vapor</h2>
<hr>

<h3>Step 7: Where's Zordak Ragefire?</h3>
<p style="color:blue">It used to be that this was where you got into the camp from Hell. Thankfully you don't have to do that anymore. Head back to the house where you found Natasha at the start of Step 5 and you'll see she's spawned again. Hand her your Message to Natasha and get your Shimmering Pearl</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul17.jpg" alt="Natasha Whitewater"><br>
<p><em>Natasha Whitewater lowers her head in mourning and whispers a prayer. It is a shame that fate has decided one so young and from such a background should perish, but we must not attempt to change what was destined to be. Priestess Naxot sacrificed herself selflessly so that others may be spared the horrors Ixiblat would have brought to Norrath. May the waters of Norrath forever remember her reflection. I thank you for delivering Naxot's message to me and give you this pearl imbued with the power of the Triumvirate. Should you find Zordak Ragefire, speak with him before all else and hand him this pearl. No mortal enemy of the Triumvirate can resist its enchantments.</em></p>
<p style="color:blue">Now head to SolB and find Zordak Ragefire. He's hiding under the bridge to the Fire Giant castle (approx loc -1400, -300). He's a 24 hour spawn down there. Hand him your Shimmering Pearl and receive Zordak's Box of Binding and a Swirling Pearl.</p>
<p><i>Zordak Ragefire is engulfed by a shimmering blue light! An inhuman expression of rage crosses his face and flames leap in his eyes as he begins to vanish in the shimmering light! 'The Triumvirate may have succeeded in sending be back to my cursed homeland for the time being! I swear to you I shall return from Skyfire and destroy all of the Triumvirate Missionaries in flames!' '</i></p>
<h3>Step 8: Zordallikus Ragefire</h3>
<p style="color:blue">Now head to Skyfire and find Warder Cecilia (p3200 n3200). She will ONLY talk to you if you have the Swirling Pearl.</p>
<p><i>Warder Cecilia says 'Greetings, you have made excellent time. We received word that Zordak was gathering his power here, and we still have little knowledge of his true intentions. Scattered throughout these mountains there are small Pearlescent Shards, binding four of these shards together within a Box of Binding should allow me to create a Seal. This seal, when fused with a Swirling Pearl inside Zordak's heart should allow our seers to divinie his true intentions, even after he has been slain. Once you have the seal I will release Zordak, make haste I will not be able to hold him for long.'</i></p>
<p style="color:blue">Pearlescent Shards drop from pretty much anything in the zone. You need 4. Once you have them, combine them inside the box of binding to form Assembled Pearlescent fragment. Hand the assembled item to Cecelia and receive Pearlescant Seal. This spawns Zordak.</p>
<strong>Zordak Ragefire(human)</strong><br>
<u>Level:</u> 55<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> ~3000<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> ~Max 75<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> CH<br>
<br>
<strong>Zordallikus Ragefire(dragon)</strong><br>
<u>Level:</u> 60<br>
<u>Hit Points:</u> 32000<br>
<u>Melee Damage:</u> Max 575<br>
<u>Spells Cast:</u> AE Fire 300 pt dd<br>
<p style="color:blue">Both are serious pushovers now with level caps and equipment being what they are. The dragon drops Impure Heart of Ragefire(which is a CONTAINER) and 2 other loots which combine Nagafen's table (including, on occasion, the coveted <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=11621">Cloak of Flames</a>) with the <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/itemlist.html?searchtext=Blazing">Blazing Armor of Fenin Ro</a> (*note* only items in that list with Fenin Ro in its name are dropped by Zordak). Combine your Swirling Pearl with the Pearlescent Seal to get the Heart of Zordak Ragefire!</p>
<img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/walkthrough/defaul34.jpg" alt="Zordak Ragefire's Heart"><br>
<p style="color:blue">Now comes the home strech... Click on!</p>
<h3><a href="index.php?page=epic104">Part 4: Orb of the Triumverate</a></h3>
</td>
</tr>
